New use case: greeting word depends on the weather
========================================================

```{r eval=FALSE}
params <- create_params(
  # ...
  weather = NA,
  temperature = NA,
) {
  list(
    # ...
    weather = weather,
    temperature =
      temperature
  )
}
```

 * Code smell: if one parameter is used, so must another

***

```{r eval=FALSE}
greet <- function(params) {
  if (!
      is.na(params$weather)
  ) {
    # Must specify both
    testit::assert(
      !is.na(
        params$temperature
      )
    )
    # ...
  }
  # ...
}
```

